<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1994-12-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Effect of template size on accumulation of defective interfering RNAs in protoplasts.</TITLE><BODY>A turnip protoplast system has been used to study the effects of template size and sequence on the replication and/or stability of a small defective interfering (DI) RNA associated with turnip crinkle virus. Our results indicated that as little as a single base difference in the size of the molecule in some regions, rather than the specific sequence, affected the level of DI RNA accumulating in protoplasts.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>